WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:03.503
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on "Promised Land"...</i>

00:03.503 --> 00:05.506
Veronica: Let's talk about how
to take back Heritage House.

00:05.506 --> 00:08.258
You have to stop limiting
yourself to your family's world.

00:08.258 --> 00:09.510
You're meant for more.

00:09.510 --> 00:10.802
Antonio: Carlos Rincón.

00:10.802 --> 00:13.138
An undocumented worker
who came here 30 years ago

00:13.138 --> 00:15.432
and took the name
Joe Sandoval.

00:15.432 --> 00:17.726
♪♪

00:17.726 --> 00:19.436
[ Workers chanting in Spanish ]

00:19.436 --> 00:20.938
Young Margaret: I know
you're in love with Joe.

00:20.938 --> 00:22.314
I'm in love with Billy.

00:22.314 --> 00:23.524
You love both of them.

00:26.902 --> 00:28.153
I'm leaving you, Joe.

00:31.073 --> 00:38.080
♪♪

00:38.080 --> 00:45.087
♪♪

00:45.087 --> 00:52.135
♪♪

00:52.135 --> 00:53.345
Ramos: Do you remember
when we were gonna add

00:53.345 --> 00:54.930
a second bedroom
to this place?

00:54.930 --> 00:57.266
Oh, Mateo wanted
a little brother.

00:57.266 --> 00:59.434
[ Chuckles ]
For two,
it's just the right size.

00:59.434 --> 01:01.436
I do love it here,
you know?

01:01.436 --> 01:03.355
But I've been thinking.

01:03.355 --> 01:06.733
Maybe we could move
back home.

01:06.733 --> 01:09.945
Buy a little place there?

01:09.945 --> 01:11.321
Sonoma?

01:11.321 --> 01:12.489
México.

01:14.116 --> 01:16.368
I mean, Junior is off to college
next year,

01:16.368 --> 01:19.830
and the truth is,
I miss it.

01:22.624 --> 01:26.044
We could even plant
a few rows there.

01:26.044 --> 01:27.087
I know.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.089
I'm asking you
to give up a lot.

01:32.092 --> 01:35.387
I would give up the world
for you.

01:37.472 --> 01:39.141
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

01:39.141 --> 01:40.642
You're gonna have to answer that
sooner or later.

01:40.642 --> 01:43.103
Yeah, I know.

01:43.103 --> 01:44.354
<i>Hola, mi amor.</i>

01:44.354 --> 01:46.064
Ma. Ma.
I was worried.

01:46.064 --> 01:47.691
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm fine.

01:47.691 --> 01:50.402
I just needed to get away
for a few days.

01:50.402 --> 01:51.903
Are you alone?

01:51.903 --> 01:55.032
No.
I'm with...someone.

01:55.866 --> 01:58.410
Uh, h-have you talked
to Joe?

01:58.410 --> 01:59.661
No.

01:59.661 --> 02:01.538
And after the way he spoke to me
the other day,

02:01.538 --> 02:04.541
I don't care if I ever hear
from him again.

02:04.541 --> 02:07.002
Okay, well, you should really
put on the news.

02:08.128 --> 02:09.296
Business Anchor:
<i>In our top story,</i>

02:09.296 --> 02:10.797
<i>shares</i>
<i>of Heritage House Vineyards</i>

02:10.797 --> 02:12.633
<i>are down 21%</i>

02:12.633 --> 02:15.135
<i>on the news that Chairman</i>
<i>of the Board Joe Sandoval</i>

02:15.135 --> 02:17.012
<i>has lived</i>
<i>in this country illegally</i>

02:17.012 --> 02:18.472
<i>for over 30 years.</i>

02:18.472 --> 02:19.723
Oh, my God.

02:19.723 --> 02:20.807
Business Anchor #2:
<i>Sandoval, a legend who</i>

02:20.807 --> 02:22.100
<i>built Heritage House into</i>

02:22.100 --> 02:24.186
<i>the country's</i>
<i>third largest wine producer,</i>

02:24.186 --> 02:28.732
<i>is, in fact, an undocumented</i>
<i>immigrant named Carlos Rincón.</i>

02:28.732 --> 02:30.192
Business Anchor #3:
<i>A number of commentators</i>

02:30.192 --> 02:31.902
<i>and several members of Congress</i>

02:31.902 --> 02:35.530
<i>have called for no amnesty or</i>
<i>special treatment for Sandoval,</i>

02:35.530 --> 02:38.742
<i>saying he should leave</i>
<i>the United States immediately.</i>

02:38.742 --> 02:41.036
Business Anchor #1: <i>It now seems</i>
<i>certain that Sandoval will lose</i>

02:41.036 --> 02:42.913
<i>his company to the woman</i>
<i>whose family</i>

02:42.913 --> 02:46.875
<i>owned Heritage House before</i>
<i>he arrived here from Mexico --</i>

02:46.875 --> 02:50.253
<i>his ex-wife, hotel magnate</i>
<i>Margaret Honeycroft.</i>

02:50.253 --> 02:51.963
She did it.

02:51.963 --> 02:55.092
[ Wind blowing ]

02:55.092 --> 02:56.718
Goodbye, Joe.

02:56.718 --> 02:58.929
Lettie.
Come back here, Lettie!

02:58.929 --> 03:00.347
Fine.
Go if you want,

03:00.347 --> 03:03.183
but don't bother
coming back!

03:03.183 --> 03:04.685
You hear me?!

03:04.685 --> 03:06.436
Juana?!

03:07.688 --> 03:10.107
[ Door closes ]
I don't want you!

03:12.776 --> 03:14.403
Veronica: No one has been
more loyal to our father

03:14.403 --> 03:17.072
than I have,
but let's face it --

03:17.072 --> 03:19.408
he's lost his way,
and so has Heritage House.

03:21.702 --> 03:25.664
It pains me to say this,
but Joe Sandoval has to go.

03:26.748 --> 03:30.210
A word of advice, <i>mija.</i>

03:30.210 --> 03:33.046
You're not the first person
to try and take me down.

03:33.046 --> 03:35.674
Sooner or later,
they all learned

03:35.674 --> 03:37.801
Joe Sandoval
isn't going anywhere.

03:37.801 --> 03:46.852
♪♪

03:46.852 --> 03:49.020
A breakaway faction.

03:49.020 --> 03:51.398
You think you can pool
your shares,

03:51.398 --> 03:53.400
get a few renegades to join you

03:53.400 --> 03:55.527
at the shareholders meeting
tomorrow.

03:55.527 --> 03:58.280
Hmm?
Let me ask you, V --

03:58.280 --> 04:00.574
if your mother hasn't been able
to force me out,

04:00.574 --> 04:02.242
and you're not half the fighter
she is,

04:02.242 --> 04:03.285
how do you expect to win?

04:03.285 --> 04:04.578
Pa.

04:04.578 --> 04:05.912
Veronica: No, Carmen,
it's okay.

04:05.912 --> 04:08.123
I've been hearing comments
like that my entire life.

04:08.123 --> 04:10.667
But that my own father
would say them is just sad.

04:10.667 --> 04:12.127
You locked out
your own workers.

04:12.127 --> 04:14.212
The damage you've done
to this company --

04:14.212 --> 04:16.256
Haven't you heard?
Tomás and I made a deal.

04:16.256 --> 04:17.466
Lockout's over.

04:17.466 --> 04:20.093
It's my job to protect
Heritage House.

04:20.093 --> 04:21.761
One you gave me.

04:21.761 --> 04:23.930
Just never thought I would have
to protect it from you.

04:23.930 --> 04:26.391
Let's see
if your siblings agree.

04:26.391 --> 04:27.642
Who's with Veronica?

04:27.642 --> 04:29.436
I am.

04:29.436 --> 04:31.104
I thought
you were smarter than that.

04:31.104 --> 04:31.897
Hm.

04:31.897 --> 04:33.815
Anyone else?

04:33.815 --> 04:35.025
[ Clears throat ]

04:35.025 --> 04:37.652
We have until tomorrow
to make our decision.

04:37.652 --> 04:39.321
I'm gonna wait until then.

04:39.321 --> 04:41.823
So will I.

04:41.823 --> 04:44.576
You made a serious mistake
heading into battle

04:44.576 --> 04:46.328
before knowing your troops
were behind you.

04:46.328 --> 04:47.370
Yeah, I guess we'll find out

04:47.370 --> 04:48.622
at the shareholders meeting,
won't we?

04:48.622 --> 04:50.499
I guess we will.

04:52.626 --> 04:54.753
My two eldest.

04:55.962 --> 04:58.465
The last people I ever thought
would betray me.

04:58.465 --> 05:01.343
You want to know
who betrayed you, Apá?

05:01.343 --> 05:02.803
Look in the mirror.

05:02.803 --> 05:09.059
♪♪

05:09.059 --> 05:09.935
Young Billy: Whoo!

05:09.935 --> 05:11.937
"Leading the striking workers,

05:11.937 --> 05:15.190
a charismatic field hand
from Jalisco, México,

05:15.190 --> 05:17.317
named Joe Sandoval."

05:17.317 --> 05:18.193
Right?

05:19.861 --> 05:22.113
La charismatic!

05:46.888 --> 05:47.848
Eh?

06:07.617 --> 06:10.245
[ Plates clattering ]

06:14.416 --> 06:17.711
<i>[ Women singing in Spanish</i>
<i>on radio ]</i>

06:39.149 --> 06:43.278
♪♪

06:45.196 --> 06:50.744
♪♪

06:50.744 --> 06:52.162
Ay.

06:52.162 --> 06:59.794
♪♪

06:59.794 --> 07:01.254
Joe...

07:01.254 --> 07:02.255
[ Sighs ]

07:02.255 --> 07:03.757
[ Plates clatter ]

07:03.757 --> 07:12.515
♪♪

07:12.515 --> 07:14.100
Hm.
[ Chuckles ]

07:19.356 --> 07:20.190
[ Laughs ]

07:20.190 --> 07:21.483
[ Speaks Spanish ]

07:23.860 --> 07:24.903
Ay.

07:27.947 --> 07:28.782
Ah!

07:33.328 --> 07:34.996
[ Laughs ]

07:38.667 --> 07:39.751
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

07:43.296 --> 07:47.425
♪♪

07:47.425 --> 07:48.802
[ Spits ]

07:48.802 --> 07:51.429
♪♪

07:53.014 --> 07:59.020
♪♪

07:59.020 --> 08:02.107
[ Birds chirping ]

08:03.817 --> 08:05.819
[ Vehicle approaching ]

08:05.819 --> 08:10.990
♪♪

08:10.990 --> 08:11.991
[ Car door opens ]

08:11.991 --> 08:14.452
♪♪

08:14.452 --> 08:16.121
Margaret: I gotta hand it
to you, Lettie.

08:16.121 --> 08:18.957
If any woman could get a priest
to break his vows...

08:18.957 --> 08:21.835
[ Chuckles ]

08:21.835 --> 08:24.254
What are
you gonna do now?

08:24.254 --> 08:28.216
Well, we're thinking of maybe
moving back to México.

08:28.216 --> 08:29.801
That should make you happy.

08:29.801 --> 08:31.720
[ Scoffs ]
Don't deny it, Margaret.

08:31.720 --> 08:34.764
With me out of the way, you can
get what you've always wanted.

08:34.764 --> 08:37.434
I don't need you to leave
to get Heritage House back.

08:37.434 --> 08:40.687
No, no, no.
I'm talking about Joe.

08:40.687 --> 08:42.731
[ Sighs ]

08:42.731 --> 08:45.316
He still loves you,
Lettie.

08:45.316 --> 08:48.862
Joe will always
love you.

08:48.862 --> 08:50.238
Once, perhaps.

08:50.238 --> 08:51.614
But not anymore.

08:51.614 --> 08:52.866
Well, I'm glad you feel
that way,

08:52.866 --> 08:56.077
because it makes what
I came here to tell you easier.

08:56.077 --> 08:57.454
Um...

08:59.247 --> 09:01.750
I know who you are,
Lettie.

09:01.750 --> 09:04.085
Or should I call you...

09:04.085 --> 09:05.503
Juana?

09:07.464 --> 09:09.299
Antonio turned over
the first stone,

09:09.299 --> 09:11.593
and I turned over a few
after that,

09:11.593 --> 09:14.596
and in a couple of days...

09:14.596 --> 09:16.890
I am going to tell
the shareholders

09:16.890 --> 09:19.100
that Joe Sandoval
is an undocumented immigrant

09:19.100 --> 09:22.228
named Carlos Rincón.

09:22.228 --> 09:24.272
Investors put their trust
in you,

09:24.272 --> 09:27.525
and when they find out
that Joe's life is a lie,

09:27.525 --> 09:29.611
they will wonder what else
he's been lying about,

09:29.611 --> 09:30.904
and they will come running
to me.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.447
But that's not what
I came here to tell you.

09:32.447 --> 09:33.740
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:33.740 --> 09:39.120
I want you to know that
I'm going to try to protect you.

09:39.120 --> 09:43.833
Just because the world
will find out the truth
about Carlos Rincón

09:43.833 --> 09:48.505
does not mean they need to know
about Juana Sánchez.

09:48.505 --> 09:51.758
Let them know.

09:51.758 --> 09:55.470
I'm not ashamed
of being Juana Sánchez.

09:55.470 --> 09:58.181
All I ask is this.

09:58.181 --> 10:00.266
You need shares.

10:00.266 --> 10:03.645
I will sell you my 5%.

10:03.645 --> 10:09.275
Just, please,
do not reveal Joe's secret.

10:09.275 --> 10:11.111
It'll destroy him.

10:11.111 --> 10:12.904
The way
he destroyed my father?

10:12.904 --> 10:14.823
Oh, please, Margaret.

10:14.823 --> 10:19.744
Years ago, I swore that I would
get that vineyard back.

10:19.744 --> 10:21.079
It's what drove me.

10:21.079 --> 10:22.831
It's the only thing I had.

10:22.831 --> 10:26.501
But not anymore.
You have your children now.

10:26.501 --> 10:30.421
You don't need
to do this.

10:30.421 --> 10:32.006
[ Sighs ]

10:32.006 --> 10:34.384
I'm sorry, Lettie.

10:34.384 --> 10:36.594
But I do.

10:36.594 --> 10:38.721
That man has
to learn a lesson.

10:40.265 --> 10:42.809
No one steals
from a Honeycroft.

10:42.809 --> 10:49.399
♪♪

10:49.399 --> 10:50.400
[ Door opens ]

10:50.400 --> 10:56.739
♪♪

10:56.739 --> 11:03.121
♪♪

11:07.834 --> 11:10.587
♪♪

11:10.587 --> 11:12.130
Veronica: Joe owns the lease
on Mateo's vineyard.

11:12.130 --> 11:14.382
He could evict him
with 60 days' notice.

11:14.382 --> 11:15.842
Mateo won't risk
pissing him off.
Yeah.

11:15.842 --> 11:17.135
We can't count
on his support.

11:17.135 --> 11:19.179
What about Carmen?
It's Carmen.

11:19.179 --> 11:21.514
She'll do what's best for her,
which is support Joe.
[ Scoffs ]

11:21.514 --> 11:22.974
So much
for the insurgency.

11:22.974 --> 11:24.517
Maybe.

11:24.517 --> 11:26.311
Maybe not.

11:26.311 --> 11:28.855
Look, we may not need
their shares.

11:28.855 --> 11:30.815
V, there's something about Apá
that you don't know.

11:30.815 --> 11:33.443
♪♪

11:33.443 --> 11:35.278
Carmen: If I pledge my shares
to Veronica,

11:35.278 --> 11:37.989
she said that she would get
behind my sangria in a big way,

11:37.989 --> 11:40.533
make it a priority
for Heritage House.

11:40.533 --> 11:42.160
And...do you
believe her?

11:42.160 --> 11:44.454
I want to.
So, no.

11:44.454 --> 11:46.915
Okay, so maybe
I go to Papi,

11:46.915 --> 11:48.458
and I get him
to make me a deal.

11:48.458 --> 11:50.043
Why does this have to be
so binary?

11:50.043 --> 11:52.587
Joe or Veronica,
what's the difference?

11:52.587 --> 11:54.464
They both
underestimate you.

11:54.464 --> 11:56.090
You got a better idea?

11:56.090 --> 11:57.634
As a matter of fact,

11:57.634 --> 12:01.179
I got a call yesterday
from Oasis Beverage.

12:01.179 --> 12:03.181
They want to make you an offer
for Gitana Sangria.

12:03.181 --> 12:05.850
[ Both laugh ]

12:05.850 --> 12:07.644
What?
Yeah.

12:07.644 --> 12:08.811
They're huge.
I know.

12:08.811 --> 12:10.271
And unlike Heritage House,

12:10.271 --> 12:12.106
they're not
just a wine company.

12:12.106 --> 12:13.900
They've got energy drinks
and hard seltzers.

12:13.900 --> 12:15.777
[ Exhales sharply ]
They could take me national.

12:15.777 --> 12:17.946
They could take you
<i>international.</i>

12:17.946 --> 12:20.156
But we gotta move fast.
Like, they want to sit down

12:20.156 --> 12:22.116
and have a meeting with you
tomorrow fast.

12:22.116 --> 12:24.535
Going outside the family.

12:24.535 --> 12:26.537
That's --
That's a big step.

12:26.537 --> 12:29.916
But it's the right step.

12:29.916 --> 12:32.168
When something
is scaring you,

12:32.168 --> 12:34.420
that's the universe telling you
that you should be doing it.

12:36.631 --> 12:38.299
Set the meeting.
Yeah?

12:38.299 --> 12:39.926
[ Laughs ]
We're meeting.
I love it.

12:39.926 --> 12:40.843
Set the meeting.

12:40.843 --> 12:41.886
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:41.886 --> 12:43.012
[ Shrieks ]

12:44.389 --> 12:46.182
<i>Hola,</i> Marta.

12:46.182 --> 12:47.642
<i>Buenas.</i>

12:54.983 --> 12:55.858
[ Door closes ]

13:05.159 --> 13:07.704
I can't wait
for this strike to be over.

13:07.704 --> 13:09.289
I miss you.

13:10.832 --> 13:12.292
I miss you, too.

13:14.335 --> 13:18.256
No. No. No. I made you
a reasonable offer.

13:20.008 --> 13:21.676
[ Sighing ] Yes.

13:21.676 --> 13:24.095
You made us <i>an</i> offer.

13:25.388 --> 13:28.433
I thought
we could have a toast.

13:28.433 --> 13:30.059
What are we toasting to?

13:30.059 --> 13:32.270
<i>Pues...</i>

13:32.270 --> 13:34.981
an end to the strike.

13:34.981 --> 13:36.816
It hurt both sides, no?

13:38.359 --> 13:39.819
[ Chuckles ]

13:40.945 --> 13:42.613
Suit yourself.

13:42.613 --> 13:43.865
I don't like blends,
either.

13:43.865 --> 13:46.200
That is
a single vineyard Cab.

13:47.201 --> 13:49.412
That's what
the label says it is.

13:49.412 --> 13:51.748
[ Chuckles ]

13:51.748 --> 13:53.791
Now, if you knew the first
damn thing about wine,

13:53.791 --> 13:55.835
you would know
the juice only has to be

13:55.835 --> 13:58.588
75% of the grape
on the label.

13:58.588 --> 14:02.091
Yes.
But this isn't.

14:02.091 --> 14:03.718
It's not even close.

14:05.011 --> 14:10.308
You see, your Cab had a virus
last year,

14:10.308 --> 14:12.101
but you don't want
nobody to know.

14:12.101 --> 14:13.895
So...

14:13.895 --> 14:15.646
you added...

14:15.646 --> 14:19.817
Merlot
for a soft base,

14:19.817 --> 14:23.196
Cab Franc for spice,

14:23.196 --> 14:27.950
and Malbec
for color and body.

14:29.994 --> 14:31.954
How the hell
can you know that?

14:31.954 --> 14:33.915
He has a good palate.

14:37.960 --> 14:42.006
♪♪

14:42.006 --> 14:44.467
You see,
Mr. Honeycroft,

14:44.467 --> 14:46.677
there's a new reporter
at the <i>Register</i>

14:46.677 --> 14:48.387
named Y. G. López,

14:48.387 --> 14:52.058
and she's been writing
some very nice stories about us.

14:52.058 --> 14:54.268
I think she'd like to know
about your, uh...

14:54.268 --> 14:55.561
[ Glass clinks ]

14:55.561 --> 14:57.814
..."single vineyard" Cab.

14:57.814 --> 15:01.025
♪♪

15:01.025 --> 15:02.944
<i>[ "El Terror de la Frontera"</i>
<i>by El Piporro playing ]</i>

15:02.944 --> 15:04.737
[ Workers whooping ]

15:04.737 --> 15:07.573
[ Fireworks exploding ]

15:07.573 --> 15:11.119
♪♪

15:11.119 --> 15:13.454
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:17.583 --> 15:19.252
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:19.252 --> 15:21.504
[ Laughing ]

15:23.297 --> 15:26.968
[ Cheering ]

15:26.968 --> 15:29.178
♪♪

15:29.178 --> 15:31.556
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:31.556 --> 15:33.099
♪ Frijol Don Salomon ♪

15:33.099 --> 15:35.309
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:35.309 --> 15:36.894
♪ Mayas rojas
para damas tristes ♪

15:36.894 --> 15:39.188
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:39.188 --> 15:40.773
♪ Zapato tacon
bajo punta chata ♪

15:40.773 --> 15:42.817
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:42.817 --> 15:44.402
♪ Calzon elastico para joven ♪

15:44.402 --> 15:46.779
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:46.779 --> 15:48.197
♪ Pastillas de esas,
para la tos ♪

15:48.197 --> 15:51.534
♪ Aquel agente viajero
tan vacilador ♪

15:51.534 --> 15:54.662
♪♪

15:55.454 --> 15:57.456
[ Sighs ]

16:05.798 --> 16:08.551
Where have you been?

16:08.551 --> 16:11.345
You told me to leave,
so I left.

16:11.345 --> 16:12.972
Were you with him?

16:15.349 --> 16:16.851
Yes.

16:19.312 --> 16:21.022
He broke his wedding vows
to you.

16:21.022 --> 16:23.399
I guess breaking his oath to God
is no big deal.

16:23.399 --> 16:25.860
What about <i>your</i> promises,
Joe?

16:25.860 --> 16:27.945
What about yours?

16:27.945 --> 16:30.364
You love saying
family always comes first.

16:30.364 --> 16:32.742
How's that working out
for you, hmm?

16:32.742 --> 16:34.869
Your own children
lining up against you.

16:38.873 --> 16:40.875
So this is how it ends,
huh?

16:41.959 --> 16:48.758
♪♪

16:48.758 --> 16:50.009
I have to pack
a few things.

16:50.009 --> 16:53.054
I can either use
one of the guest bedrooms

16:53.054 --> 16:57.141
or stay at a hotel.

16:57.141 --> 16:58.976
It's your house.

16:58.976 --> 17:06.067
♪♪

17:06.067 --> 17:07.318
Veronica: My God.

17:07.318 --> 17:10.613
To live with a secret like that
all those years.

17:10.613 --> 17:12.740
Yeah.
Joe's no fool.

17:12.740 --> 17:14.700
He knows what would happen
if it ever got out he's illegal.

17:14.700 --> 17:15.826
Oh, I don't like
that word.

17:15.826 --> 17:17.578
Yeah, and I despise it.

17:17.578 --> 17:18.955
But that's what
they're gonna call him.

17:18.955 --> 17:21.082
The media,
the shareholders.

17:21.082 --> 17:22.124
[ Sighs ]

17:22.124 --> 17:24.752
V, I told Margaret
about this.

17:24.752 --> 17:27.713
If we don't use it,
she will.

17:27.713 --> 17:29.173
The shareholders
will run to her,

17:29.173 --> 17:30.967
and she'll take over
the company.

17:30.967 --> 17:32.468
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:34.804 --> 17:37.723
If the tables were turned,

17:37.723 --> 17:41.727
if Joe had this information
about an opponent...

17:41.727 --> 17:44.063
He would use it
without hesitation.

17:44.063 --> 17:47.525
♪♪

17:47.525 --> 17:50.152
Then we use it.

17:50.152 --> 17:51.696
[ Fireworks exploding,
people cheering ]

17:51.696 --> 17:54.240
[ "Mi Tierra" by
Mariachi Suspiros Mexicanos
playing muffled ]

17:54.240 --> 17:55.616
[ Exhales shakily ]

17:55.616 --> 17:58.911
♪♪

17:58.911 --> 18:00.288
[ Sighs ]

18:00.288 --> 18:01.080
[ Door closes ]

18:01.080 --> 18:02.248
[ Gasps ]

18:02.248 --> 18:03.416
♪♪

18:03.416 --> 18:04.458
Young Lettie: Hey.

18:05.710 --> 18:10.923
♪♪

18:10.923 --> 18:13.050
I thought
I knew what I wanted.

18:13.050 --> 18:14.135
Billy.

18:14.135 --> 18:16.220
The vineyard,
the house on the hill.

18:16.220 --> 18:17.805
But now I know.

18:17.805 --> 18:20.683
What I really wanted
is to be with you.

18:20.683 --> 18:21.851
[ Sighs ]

18:21.851 --> 18:23.311
♪♪

18:30.151 --> 18:31.402
Billy...

18:31.402 --> 18:36.490
♪♪

18:38.075 --> 18:45.791
♪♪

18:45.791 --> 18:48.294
[ Breathes shakily ]

18:55.134 --> 18:56.636
Lettie.

18:58.095 --> 18:58.971
<i>Oye.</i>

19:05.811 --> 19:07.104
No, no, no, no!

19:22.411 --> 19:23.496
[ Grunts ]

19:23.496 --> 19:26.040
♪♪

19:26.040 --> 19:26.916
Lettie!

19:32.254 --> 19:33.631
Oasis CEO: From the moment
I saw the bottle,

19:33.631 --> 19:35.925
I knew a special creative force
was behind it.

19:35.925 --> 19:37.426
Then I saw your P and L's,

19:37.426 --> 19:41.013
and I knew this is exactly
what we've been looking for.
Mm-hmm.

19:41.013 --> 19:43.683
So, you've heard what a company
of our scope can do

19:43.683 --> 19:45.309
for Gitana Sangria,
Carmen.

19:45.309 --> 19:47.478
Now, let me tell you
what we're prepared to do

19:47.478 --> 19:50.690
to bring you into
the Oasis Beverage family.

19:50.690 --> 19:52.733
A purchase price
of $19 million.

19:52.733 --> 19:54.902
That's a valuation
one-and-a-half times greater

19:54.902 --> 19:57.863
than your own investment banker
says the company's worth.

19:57.863 --> 20:00.783
Plus, stock options exercisable
in five years.

20:00.783 --> 20:03.577
If those options were converted
at yesterday's closing price,

20:03.577 --> 20:05.496
you'd receive an additional
$60 million.

20:08.082 --> 20:10.209
That's a lot of money.

20:10.209 --> 20:12.795
But that's not
why I do this.

20:12.795 --> 20:15.297
Well, that's why we'd like you
to come on board

20:15.297 --> 20:17.174
as Gitana's
chief creative officer.

20:17.174 --> 20:18.592
So you'd still be doing
the work you love.

20:18.592 --> 20:21.095
You'd just be a hell
of a lot richer doing it.

20:21.095 --> 20:23.723
[ Both laugh ]

20:23.723 --> 20:24.849
There's one catch.

20:24.849 --> 20:27.184
Uh, we'd like to launch
a national ad campaign,

20:27.184 --> 20:29.311
and working back
from the Super Bowl,

20:29.311 --> 20:31.689
we'd need to get
that effort started,

20:31.689 --> 20:33.190
well, yesterday,
really.
Woman: Mm-hmm.

20:33.190 --> 20:37.069
[ Inhales sharply ]
We need to move fast, Carmen.

20:37.069 --> 20:38.404
Like, today.

20:38.404 --> 20:46.245
♪♪

20:46.245 --> 20:47.872
This is really fast.

20:47.872 --> 20:49.206
I'm not saying
that it isn't.

20:49.206 --> 20:50.458
I should have someone
look at it.

20:50.458 --> 20:51.876
Heritage House
counsel or --

20:51.876 --> 20:53.544
Daddy's lawyer?

20:53.544 --> 20:55.796
Carmen, when are you gonna
stand on your own?

20:55.796 --> 20:57.423
This is an incredible
opportunity,

20:57.423 --> 20:59.467
and it's not
gonna knock twice.

20:59.467 --> 21:01.302
These people
want to move.

21:01.302 --> 21:02.511
Trust me.

21:02.511 --> 21:04.180
[ Sighs ]

21:04.180 --> 21:08.559
♪♪

21:08.559 --> 21:10.311
<i>Las herramientas</i>
<i>para mañana.</i>

21:10.311 --> 21:11.687
<i>Vale.</i>
Man: <i>Sí, señora.</i>

21:11.687 --> 21:13.063
[ Car door closes ]

21:13.063 --> 21:14.106
[ Giggles ]

21:14.106 --> 21:15.274
Hi, Mommy.

21:15.274 --> 21:17.359
Hi.

21:17.359 --> 21:18.652
Alright,
I'll see you next week.

21:18.652 --> 21:19.653
No.
Hi.

21:19.653 --> 21:21.155
No, you won't.
[ Rita babbling ]

21:21.155 --> 21:22.323
What do you mean?

21:22.323 --> 21:23.783
You win, V.

21:23.783 --> 21:24.825
You want sole custody?

21:24.825 --> 21:26.994
Fine.
Just call your dogs off.

21:26.994 --> 21:29.497
I haven't put any "dogs"
on you, Michael.

21:29.497 --> 21:31.040
Yeah, right.
Knowing you, you probably had

21:31.040 --> 21:33.209
Daddy or Margaret do it
for you, huh?

21:33.209 --> 21:34.752
Well,
you can tell them to stop.

21:34.752 --> 21:36.378
I'm done.

21:38.839 --> 21:40.132
[ Coos ]

21:40.132 --> 21:41.133
Michael.

21:41.133 --> 21:42.510
Bye, Daddy.
[ Car door opens ]

21:43.761 --> 21:45.971
[ Car door closes,
engine starts ]

21:49.141 --> 21:53.896
♪♪

21:55.314 --> 21:56.857
Young Veronica: <i>Ah, sí?</i>

21:56.857 --> 21:59.193
Young Joe: Ah, <i>sí.</i>
Ah.

21:59.193 --> 22:01.028
[ Speaks Spanish ]

22:03.239 --> 22:08.035
♪♪

22:08.035 --> 22:12.790
♪♪

22:12.790 --> 22:14.500
[ Young Joe speaking Spanish ]

22:16.961 --> 22:18.379
That's it, Papi.

22:18.379 --> 22:25.719
♪♪

22:25.719 --> 22:26.971
[ Sighs ]

22:26.971 --> 22:29.181
Hello. <i>Hola.</i>

22:29.181 --> 22:30.391
Hey.

22:30.391 --> 22:31.892
Hey, <i>mi amor.</i>

22:31.892 --> 22:33.561
How's the punchdown
going?

22:33.561 --> 22:36.730
Joe was nice enough
to lend me one of his vats.

22:36.730 --> 22:38.357
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

22:38.357 --> 22:40.401
And by nice enough,
I mean he thinks it'll get me

22:40.401 --> 22:41.443
to pledge him my shares.

22:41.443 --> 22:43.070
[ Chuckles ]

22:43.070 --> 22:45.447
What are you gonna do?

22:45.447 --> 22:47.241
[ Sighs ]
I don't know.

22:47.241 --> 22:49.201
I've had my problems with Joe,
obviously,

22:49.201 --> 22:52.371
but seeing what he's built and
knowing now what that takes --

22:52.371 --> 22:53.914
Veronica and Antonio
never had to do that.

22:53.914 --> 22:55.791
Mm.

22:55.791 --> 22:57.543
But the real question is,
what are you gonna do, Ma?

23:00.921 --> 23:04.550
Well, you know, last week,
at the harvest,

23:04.550 --> 23:07.428
working the vines,

23:07.428 --> 23:11.891
I felt something I hadn't felt
for a long, long time.

23:14.101 --> 23:18.689
We're thinking of maybe
moving back to México,

23:18.689 --> 23:20.524
planting a few rows.

23:21.692 --> 23:23.193
Ma.

23:23.193 --> 23:25.946
Look, I'm not gonna
tell you what to do

23:25.946 --> 23:28.240
or where to go
or who to go with,

23:28.240 --> 23:31.327
but...

23:31.327 --> 23:32.578
if you're just planting
a few rows,

23:32.578 --> 23:35.331
why do you
need anybody?

23:35.331 --> 23:36.957
[ Stammers ]

23:36.957 --> 23:39.543
I mean, you've given your whole
life to your family, Mama.

23:39.543 --> 23:42.004
To Billy, then to Joe,
then to me.

23:46.091 --> 23:47.635
When is it gonna be
your turn?

23:47.635 --> 23:50.304
♪♪

23:50.304 --> 23:51.931
Hmm.

23:51.931 --> 23:54.391
♪♪

23:54.391 --> 23:55.726
<i>[ Monitor warbles ]</i>

23:55.726 --> 23:57.770
Ultrasound Tech:
The home test was right.

23:57.770 --> 24:01.273
11 or 12 weeks,
by the looks of him.

24:01.273 --> 24:02.149
Him?

24:03.275 --> 24:04.860
It's a boy.

24:13.118 --> 24:15.079
The doctor will be in
to discuss your options.

24:16.372 --> 24:17.414
Thank you.

24:18.666 --> 24:21.085
[ Door opens, closes ]
[ Sighs ]

24:24.213 --> 24:25.839
Thank you
for coming with me.

24:25.839 --> 24:27.925
That's what
friends are for.

24:27.925 --> 24:29.510
[ Sighs ]

24:29.510 --> 24:33.138
Lettie...

24:33.138 --> 24:34.306
I have to ask.

24:36.475 --> 24:37.851
It's Billy's.

24:37.851 --> 24:42.022
♪♪

24:42.022 --> 24:43.649
What are you going to do?

24:43.649 --> 24:48.862
♪♪

24:48.862 --> 24:50.406
I thought it only happened
in books --

24:50.406 --> 24:51.991
falling in love
with two brothers.

24:51.991 --> 24:55.786
♪♪

24:55.786 --> 24:57.705
Billy --

24:57.705 --> 24:59.206
he has a light
inside him.

24:59.206 --> 25:01.375
When he smiles,
I feel so happy.

25:03.377 --> 25:05.254
But Joe...

25:05.254 --> 25:08.507
♪♪

25:08.507 --> 25:11.844
Joe --
when he looks at me, I...

25:11.844 --> 25:13.971
I know that anything
is possible.

25:13.971 --> 25:16.515
♪♪

25:16.515 --> 25:19.351
What are you going to do,
Lettie?

25:19.351 --> 25:25.274
♪♪

25:25.274 --> 25:27.901
I couldn't choose,
so God chose for me.

25:27.901 --> 25:31.113
♪♪

25:31.113 --> 25:33.490
I'm going
to name him Mateo.

25:33.490 --> 25:37.244
♪♪

25:37.244 --> 25:41.081
♪♪

25:56.597 --> 25:57.973
<i>Sí.</i>

25:58.974 --> 26:01.101
[ Speaks Spanish ]
[ Both laughing ]

26:01.101 --> 26:02.102
Billy!

26:02.102 --> 26:03.312
Sorry! Sorry!
Sorry, sorry, sorry!

26:03.312 --> 26:04.438
Sorry, sorry.

26:05.522 --> 26:07.066
[ Laughs ]

26:08.317 --> 26:09.359
<i>Sí.</i>

26:17.034 --> 26:24.458
♪♪

26:30.964 --> 26:34.301
Antonio: It's so barren.

26:34.301 --> 26:37.179
Javi:
I think it's beautiful.

26:37.179 --> 26:39.681
There's a quote I love.

26:39.681 --> 26:41.892
"A vineyard in winter
looks like hope."

26:41.892 --> 26:44.478
♪♪

26:44.478 --> 26:45.604
Well, that was poetic.

26:45.604 --> 26:47.940
[ Both chuckle ]

26:47.940 --> 26:49.483
Where'd you hear that?

26:49.483 --> 26:51.151
Your father.

26:51.151 --> 26:57.825
♪♪

26:57.825 --> 27:04.456
♪♪

27:04.456 --> 27:05.707
-Hey.
-Hey.

27:08.127 --> 27:10.879
[ Laughs ]

27:48.584 --> 27:50.002
<i>Sí.</i>

28:04.141 --> 28:05.851
Joe...

28:14.401 --> 28:22.034
♪♪

28:22.034 --> 28:23.493
[ Grunts ]

28:23.493 --> 28:29.708
♪♪

28:33.754 --> 28:35.380
<i>Sí.</i>

28:35.380 --> 28:41.011
♪♪

28:58.528 --> 29:01.365
♪♪

29:01.365 --> 29:02.783
No.
No, no, no.

29:02.783 --> 29:03.742
<i>Oye,</i> Lettie.

29:18.924 --> 29:20.258
No, no.
Leticia --

29:20.258 --> 29:21.927
No.

29:23.637 --> 29:24.513
Lettie.

29:27.140 --> 29:28.600
No, Joe.

29:29.476 --> 29:30.894
Letici-- Lettie.

29:39.111 --> 29:42.239
♪♪

29:44.324 --> 29:48.870
♪♪

29:48.870 --> 29:51.373
[ Sobbing ]

29:51.373 --> 29:59.965
♪♪

29:59.965 --> 30:08.640
♪♪

30:08.640 --> 30:17.315
♪♪

30:17.315 --> 30:18.984
We're even now.

30:18.984 --> 30:22.362
I took your dream,
the house, the vineyard.

30:22.362 --> 30:24.489
You took Lettie.

30:26.992 --> 30:28.785
It doesn't work like that,
Joe.

30:36.168 --> 30:44.384
♪♪

30:44.384 --> 30:52.559
♪♪

30:52.559 --> 31:00.817
♪♪

31:00.817 --> 31:08.992
♪♪

31:08.992 --> 31:11.078
I'm -- I'm sorry, uh,
about the mess,

31:11.078 --> 31:13.663
but Marta is gonna
ship everything to me.

31:13.663 --> 31:15.582
You're not going to
the shareholders meeting?

31:18.085 --> 31:20.754
I pledged my shares
to Veronica.

31:20.754 --> 31:22.422
It won't give her
full control,

31:22.422 --> 31:25.383
but neither you nor Margaret
deserve Heritage House.

31:27.511 --> 31:28.845
Just each other.

31:28.845 --> 31:34.059
♪♪

31:34.059 --> 31:35.227
Goodbye, Joe.

31:35.227 --> 31:36.686
Lettie.

31:36.686 --> 31:39.940
♪♪

31:39.940 --> 31:41.483
Don't go.

31:41.483 --> 31:44.277
♪♪

31:50.117 --> 31:56.665
♪♪

31:56.665 --> 32:03.171
♪♪

32:03.171 --> 32:04.422
[ Door closes ]

32:04.422 --> 32:08.468
♪♪

32:13.306 --> 32:14.641
[ Glass shatters ]

32:15.392 --> 32:16.852
[ Clattering ]

32:21.439 --> 32:23.108
[ Breathing heavily ]

32:23.108 --> 32:26.403
[ Grunting ]

32:33.493 --> 32:38.999
♪♪

32:38.999 --> 32:44.462
♪♪

32:44.462 --> 32:46.631
[ Groans ]

32:46.631 --> 32:53.096
♪♪

32:53.096 --> 32:59.519
♪♪

32:59.519 --> 33:06.026
♪♪

33:06.026 --> 33:10.030
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:10.030 --> 33:12.324
Veronica:
<i>Hola. Buenas tardes.</i>

33:12.324 --> 33:14.242
Good afternoon,
ladies and gentlemen.

33:14.242 --> 33:16.995
Welcome to our annual
shareholders meeting

33:16.995 --> 33:19.539
for Heritage House Vineyards.

33:19.539 --> 33:21.166
Whether you're here with us
in Sonoma

33:21.166 --> 33:25.003
or one of the thousands
joining us remotely,

33:25.003 --> 33:26.922
we're very happy
you could make it.

33:26.922 --> 33:30.759
Now, today, we will be electing
six new directors to the board,

33:30.759 --> 33:32.427
but before we do that,
I would like to start

33:32.427 --> 33:33.261
by inviting you
to please --

33:33.261 --> 33:37.432
[ Wine glass clanging ]

33:37.432 --> 33:38.516
Point of order.

33:38.516 --> 33:40.352
Yes?

33:43.230 --> 33:44.898
Under
the Heritage House bylaws,

33:44.898 --> 33:46.983
anyone that owns
30% of the common stock

33:46.983 --> 33:50.737
has the right to address
the shareholders.

33:50.737 --> 33:52.989
Given the recent
labor conflict

33:52.989 --> 33:55.909
and the generally shoddy way
the current chairman,

33:55.909 --> 34:01.122
Mr. Joe Sandoval,
has performed his duties,

34:01.122 --> 34:02.999
I invoke this right.

34:02.999 --> 34:05.293
[ Crowd murmuring ]

34:05.293 --> 34:08.588
♪♪

34:08.588 --> 34:11.508
A one-hour window will be
set aside for this purpose.

34:11.508 --> 34:14.719
Ms. Honeycroft can address
the shareholders after lunch.

34:14.719 --> 34:18.181
♪♪

34:18.181 --> 34:19.349
It's time.

34:19.349 --> 34:22.060
We need to know
your decision.

34:22.060 --> 34:23.520
I mean,
my hands are tied.

34:23.520 --> 34:25.814
The trustee pledged my shares
to Dad.

34:25.814 --> 34:27.732
Car?

34:27.732 --> 34:29.901
Can we help you take Gitana
to the next level?

34:29.901 --> 34:31.569
I'm sorry, V.

34:31.569 --> 34:33.780
I got a better offer.

34:33.780 --> 34:35.615
From Pa?

34:35.615 --> 34:36.658
No.

34:36.658 --> 34:39.536
Oasis Beverage.

34:39.536 --> 34:42.163
And I've thought
long and hard about this,

34:42.163 --> 34:44.457
but I'm moving on,

34:44.457 --> 34:47.002
and I'm not gonna take down Papi
on my way out.

34:49.254 --> 34:50.338
Mateo,
that leaves you.

34:51.423 --> 34:54.968
Joe built this company.

34:54.968 --> 34:56.511
I respect you guys,
but I can't be a part

34:56.511 --> 34:57.762
of taking that away
from him.

34:59.931 --> 35:00.974
I'm sorry.

35:00.974 --> 35:03.852
♪♪

35:03.852 --> 35:04.894
<i>Suerte.</i>

35:04.894 --> 35:11.026
♪♪

35:11.026 --> 35:12.235
[ Sighs ]

35:12.235 --> 35:14.696
That's it, then.

35:14.696 --> 35:16.489
We either tell the world
about Joe and blow him up

35:16.489 --> 35:20.285
or let Margaret do it.

35:20.285 --> 35:22.078
You know how we said
if the tables were turned,

35:22.078 --> 35:24.331
he wouldn't hesitate
to use this information?

35:24.331 --> 35:25.999
Yeah.

35:25.999 --> 35:27.959
Now I think...

35:27.959 --> 35:29.753
That's exactly
why we can't use it?

35:29.753 --> 35:31.129
Yeah.
Yeah.

35:32.589 --> 35:34.132
There's another way.

35:34.132 --> 35:37.427
♪♪

35:37.427 --> 35:40.180
Alright, I'm listening.

35:40.180 --> 35:42.599
You control 39% of voting shares
in this company.

35:42.599 --> 35:43.767
Mm-hmm.
12 more

35:43.767 --> 35:45.143
and you can ram your own
slate of directors through

35:45.143 --> 35:46.770
and force Joe out.

35:46.770 --> 35:49.397
We control 15
with Lettie's.

35:49.397 --> 35:50.690
We'll give you control
of Heritage House

35:50.690 --> 35:52.525
under two conditions.

35:52.525 --> 35:55.111
The first, <i>we</i> run
the day-to-day operations.

35:55.111 --> 35:57.030
I'll head
the wine division,

35:57.030 --> 35:59.532
and Antonio will spearhead
the new spirits division.

35:59.532 --> 36:01.660
One word -- tequila.

36:01.660 --> 36:02.744
What's my role?

36:02.744 --> 36:03.953
Purely advisory.

36:03.953 --> 36:06.039
You do have a chain
of hotels to run.

36:06.039 --> 36:07.374
What's the second condition?

36:07.374 --> 36:12.712
The name Carlos Rincón
remains our secret forever.

36:12.712 --> 36:15.757
You know,
I may not need your 15%.

36:15.757 --> 36:18.301
Once I drop
the Carlos Rincón bomb,

36:18.301 --> 36:21.179
I think more than a few
shareholders will come my way.

36:21.179 --> 36:22.472
Hmm.
Maybe.

36:22.472 --> 36:23.890
Yeah.
Hm.

36:23.890 --> 36:26.810
But then you'd have to run
this place all by yourself.

36:26.810 --> 36:28.520
Yeah.
That's a big job.

36:28.520 --> 36:29.562
Pretty hard.

36:29.562 --> 36:31.731
Yeah, it might not leave you
a lot of time

36:31.731 --> 36:33.483
to get to know
your granddaughter.

36:33.483 --> 36:36.027
Or your family.
Be a shame.

36:36.027 --> 36:37.404
Wow.

36:37.404 --> 36:38.655
Moral high ground
one minute,

36:38.655 --> 36:40.073
emotional blackmail
the next.

36:40.073 --> 36:42.534
You really are
daddy's little girl.

36:42.534 --> 36:43.576
[ Chuckles ]

36:45.120 --> 36:47.497
It's a deal.

36:47.497 --> 36:50.125
It'll be nice working
with my children.

36:50.125 --> 36:52.210
Hmm.

36:52.210 --> 36:54.838
In a purely <i>advisory</i> role,
of course.

36:54.838 --> 36:56.005
[ Chuckles ]

36:56.005 --> 36:59.050
Woman: ...Joe Sandoval.
[ Applause ]

36:59.050 --> 37:04.764
♪♪

37:04.764 --> 37:10.437
♪♪

37:10.437 --> 37:11.438
Thanks so much.

37:11.438 --> 37:13.273
It's wonderful
to see you all,

37:13.273 --> 37:14.524
especially my children.

37:19.362 --> 37:20.864
In front of you,
you'll see a copy

37:20.864 --> 37:23.950
of our company's
annual report.

37:23.950 --> 37:27.662
I regret to say,
it contains a lie.

37:27.662 --> 37:29.789
Not on our balance sheet.

37:29.789 --> 37:31.124
Despite what
you may have heard,

37:31.124 --> 37:33.710
Heritage House
has never been stronger.

37:33.710 --> 37:35.253
No.

37:35.253 --> 37:38.256
This lie is
right on the first page,

37:38.256 --> 37:40.091
next to a picture
of my face.

37:40.091 --> 37:41.718
"My Story."

37:41.718 --> 37:45.096
It says I was born
in Jalisco, México,

37:45.096 --> 37:47.182
and that's true enough.

37:47.182 --> 37:48.433
I'll be damned.

37:48.433 --> 37:49.893
Stop him.

37:51.060 --> 37:54.147
But I didn't come here
on the guest worker program.

37:55.982 --> 37:58.109
I came over the Wall.

37:58.109 --> 37:59.486
[ Crowd murmuring ]

37:59.486 --> 38:02.280
And my real name
isn't Joe Sandoval.

38:04.365 --> 38:06.034
It's Carlos Rincón.

38:06.034 --> 38:07.285
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:07.285 --> 38:10.747
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

38:10.747 --> 38:13.208
I lied to you.

38:13.208 --> 38:16.795
And I am so sorry for that.

38:16.795 --> 38:19.255
I was scared
that if the truth got out,

38:19.255 --> 38:21.883
I'd lose everything
I've built.

38:21.883 --> 38:23.134
I lost sight of the fact

38:23.134 --> 38:25.470
that the most important thing
I've built,

38:25.470 --> 38:28.723
no man could ever take away.

38:28.723 --> 38:32.185
But I am not sorry
for coming here.

38:32.185 --> 38:35.563
For working hard,
or building this company.

38:35.563 --> 38:38.191
I am not sorry for paying taxes,

38:38.191 --> 38:40.860
for giving hundreds
of people jobs,

38:40.860 --> 38:46.574
or for making some of you
<i>very</i> rich.

38:46.574 --> 38:48.701
For chasing the dream?

38:48.701 --> 38:51.204
You'll never hear me
apologize for that.

38:51.204 --> 38:57.669
So, to the people who will say
I don't belong here,

38:57.669 --> 39:00.296
that I'm illegal...

39:01.923 --> 39:04.300
If wanting a better life
for me and my children

39:04.300 --> 39:07.011
makes me illegal,

39:07.011 --> 39:09.556
then I'll wear the name
with pride.

39:09.556 --> 39:12.141
You want to deport me?

39:12.141 --> 39:14.978
I've got a mountain of money,

39:14.978 --> 39:16.312
an army of lawyers,

39:16.312 --> 39:19.023
and two U. S. senators
on speed dial.

39:19.023 --> 39:20.400
Please.

39:20.400 --> 39:24.195
<i>Try</i> to deport me.

39:24.195 --> 39:27.574
In the meantime,
there are millions of immigrants

39:27.574 --> 39:31.244
living in this country who don't
have my money or my lawyers.

39:31.244 --> 39:34.289
If past is prologue,

39:34.289 --> 39:36.583
I'm sure
you'll go after them instead.

39:38.042 --> 39:41.462
150 years ago,
it was the Irish,

39:41.462 --> 39:43.965
then the Germans,

39:43.965 --> 39:45.800
the Italians,

39:45.800 --> 39:47.176
the Jews.

39:47.176 --> 39:50.346
Right now,
it happens to be my people.

39:50.346 --> 39:54.100
A term I used to reject.
[ Scoffs ]

39:54.100 --> 39:55.727
But not anymore.

39:58.062 --> 40:01.524
You may get these people
to leave,

40:01.524 --> 40:07.113
but you will never stamp out
the thing that brings them here.

40:09.157 --> 40:11.993
You can't deport a dream.

40:11.993 --> 40:15.121
[ Chuckles ]

40:15.121 --> 40:19.375
You can't keep it out
with a Wall

40:19.375 --> 40:21.294
or a law

40:21.294 --> 40:22.879
or a slur.

40:25.506 --> 40:28.760
Because this dream doesn't live
on one side of the border

40:28.760 --> 40:31.095
or the other.

40:31.095 --> 40:32.722
It lives here.

40:32.722 --> 40:40.063
♪♪

40:40.063 --> 40:47.403
♪♪

40:50.073 --> 40:51.699
♪♪

40:51.699 --> 40:55.870
And that is a light
that never goes out.

40:55.870 --> 41:02.919
♪♪

41:18.685 --> 41:20.895
I gave Marta the day off.

41:28.736 --> 41:31.906
Uh, the shareholders aren't
voting until the morning.

41:31.906 --> 41:35.451
Maybe they'll --
Shareholders aren't exactly
known for their courage.

41:35.451 --> 41:38.121
I think we both know
how that's gonna go.

41:38.121 --> 41:40.248
I didn't want to win
like this.

41:40.248 --> 41:42.291
Like what?

41:42.291 --> 41:46.421
You throw
a hell of a punch, V.

41:46.421 --> 41:48.756
But your first punch
is always love.

41:50.800 --> 41:54.971
That's why you're a better
leader than I could ever be.

41:54.971 --> 41:57.890
♪♪

41:57.890 --> 42:00.018
It's your time now.

42:01.310 --> 42:02.895
[ Exhales sharply ]

42:02.895 --> 42:09.235
♪♪

42:09.235 --> 42:15.533
♪♪

42:15.533 --> 42:18.661
Oh, I need a drink.

42:18.661 --> 42:21.497
You heard about
the shareholders meeting?

42:21.497 --> 42:22.749
It was awful.

42:25.376 --> 42:26.919
[ Clears throat ]

42:29.547 --> 42:31.049
What's the matter?

42:31.049 --> 42:35.219
The, uh --
The Oasis people called.

42:35.219 --> 42:36.721
They're gonna table
Gitana.

42:38.347 --> 42:40.308
Table it? What do you mean?
They just bought it.

42:40.308 --> 42:44.020
Yeah, they have their own
sangria that they're gonna push.

42:44.020 --> 42:45.646
There's a campaign
and everything.

42:45.646 --> 42:47.190
They've been planning it
for months.

42:47.190 --> 42:49.776
You mean they bought Gitana just
so that they could shelve it?

42:49.776 --> 42:51.360
So I couldn't compete
against them?

42:51.360 --> 42:53.154
Yeah.

42:53.154 --> 42:54.572
I feel horrible.

42:54.572 --> 42:56.115
Yeah, well, you should.

42:56.115 --> 42:58.159
Hey, you don't need to raise
your voice at me.

42:58.159 --> 42:59.869
Don't raise my voice at you,
Nati?

42:59.869 --> 43:01.579
No, don't.

43:02.789 --> 43:05.124
I put everything
into that sangria.

43:05.124 --> 43:07.543
I finally had something
that was mine,

43:07.543 --> 43:09.337
not my family's.

43:09.337 --> 43:11.631
And who do you think helped
push you to get it there?

43:13.841 --> 43:15.927
You knew, didn't you?

43:15.927 --> 43:17.386
[ Scoffs ]

43:17.386 --> 43:18.596
What?

43:18.596 --> 43:20.890
You knew!

43:20.890 --> 43:23.267
How could you even think that
of me, Carmen?

43:25.603 --> 43:26.521
Are you --

43:27.939 --> 43:28.940
Carmen.

43:28.940 --> 43:29.816
Carmen!

43:29.816 --> 43:31.317
Carmen, wait!

43:31.317 --> 43:34.445
♪♪

43:34.445 --> 43:35.780
[ Door slams ]

43:35.780 --> 43:44.539
♪♪

43:44.539 --> 43:53.297
♪♪

43:53.297 --> 43:57.260
10 years we were married,
Joe.

43:57.260 --> 44:00.012
Why didn't you tell me?

44:00.012 --> 44:02.140
Did I make you feel like
you couldn't tell me?

44:02.140 --> 44:04.267
You made me feel like
a king.

44:04.267 --> 44:06.394
[ Sighs ]

44:08.396 --> 44:11.732
Anyway, what difference
would it have made?

44:11.732 --> 44:13.693
I guess
we'll never know.

44:19.282 --> 44:22.285
What are you
gonna do now?

44:22.285 --> 44:24.871
I mean, besides be
the biggest

44:24.871 --> 44:28.791
pain-in-the-ass minority
shareholder in the world.

44:30.168 --> 44:31.711
Do?
Mm-hmm.

44:33.045 --> 44:35.506
This is all I know
how to do.

44:37.717 --> 44:39.802
I'm done
with Heritage House.

44:39.802 --> 44:44.015
♪♪

44:44.015 --> 44:45.808
I want you to buy me out.

44:45.808 --> 44:48.352
♪♪

44:48.352 --> 44:49.896
[ Sighs ]

44:49.896 --> 44:54.901
20 years I've been waiting
for you to say those words.

44:54.901 --> 44:57.403
[ Sighs ]

44:57.403 --> 44:58.946
But now that you have...

44:58.946 --> 45:01.616
♪♪

45:01.616 --> 45:02.992
Uh...

45:02.992 --> 45:10.082
♪♪

45:10.082 --> 45:11.542
Goodbye, Margaret.

45:13.794 --> 45:14.670
Mm.

45:14.670 --> 45:19.467
♪♪

